						<h4>Chiara Barzini</h4>
												<p>Chiara Barzini is an Italian author and screenwriter. Her work has appeared in <em>Bomb, Noon, Harper’s, ZYZZYVA, Freeman's, Vogue, T Magazine, Vice, Rolling Stone, Interview Magazine</em>, and others. She is the author of the story collection <em>Sister Stop Breathing</em> (Calamari Press, 2012) and the novel <em>Things That Happened Before The Earthquake</em> (Doubleday, 2017). She lives in Rome.</p>
